23 SECTION 5.10.(a) G.S. 58-51-57 is recodified as G.S. 58-3-271.
24 SECTION 5.10.(b) G.S. 58-3-271, as enacted by subsection (a) of this section, reads
25 as rewritten:
26 "§ 58-3-271. Coverage for diagnostic, screening, and supplemental examinations for
27 breast cancer, including mammograms and other imaging, and cervical cancer
28 screening.
29 (a) The following definitions apply in this section:
30 (1) Breast magnetic resonance imaging. – A diagnostic tool that uses a powerful
31 magnetic field, radio waves, and a computer to produce detailed pictures of
32 the structures within the breast.
33 (2) Breast ultrasound. – A noninvasive diagnostic tool that uses high-frequency
34 sound waves to produce detailed images of the breast.
35 (3) Cost-sharing. – A deductible, coinsurance, copayment, and any maximum
36 limitation on the application of a deductible, coinsurance, copayment, or
37 similar out-of-pocket expense.
38 (4) Diagnostic examination for breast cancer. – An examination for breast cancer
39 that is determined by the healthcare provider treating the patient to be
40 medically necessary and appropriate and that may include breast magnetic
41 resonance imaging, breast ultrasound, and diagnostic low-dose
42 mammography to evaluate the abnormality in the breast that meets one of the
43 following criteria:
44 a. Is seen or suspected from a screening examination for breast cancer.
45 b. Is detected by another means of examination.
46 (5) High-deductible health plan. – As defined under the Internal Revenue Code.
47 (6) Low-dose mammography. – A radiologic procedure for the early detection of
48 breast cancer using equipment dedicated specifically for mammography,
49 including a physician's interpretation of the results of the procedure.
