13 SECTION 5.15.(c) Implementation. – Notwithstanding Section 310, Residential
14 Group R, of the North Carolina Building Code, and Section 203.10, Residential Group R, of the
15 North Carolina Fire Code, a family child care home located within a dwelling subject to the North
16 Carolina Building Code shall be treated as a Residential Group R-3 occupancy. The dwelling
17 where the family child care home is located shall be permitted to comply with the North Carolina
18 Building Code, provided that a family child care home must meet only the following additional
19 requirements:
20 (1) Rooms and areas within a family child care home where occupants receive
21 care shall be on the same level of exit discharge.
22 (2) Rooms and areas within a family child care home where occupants receive
23 care shall be located on the same level with, and within a maximum of 40 feet
24 travel distance to, at least one 2A:10B:C fire extinguisher.
25 (3) A family child care home shall have and maintain a Fire Safety, Evacuation,
26 and Lockdown Plan compliant with Section 404 of the North Carolina Fire
27 Code.
28 (4) A family child care home shall have carbon monoxide alarm and detection
29 systems compliant with Section 915 of the North Carolina Building Code.
30 (5) A family child care home shall have smoke alarms compliant with Section
31 R907 of the North Carolina Building Code.
