15 transfer the amount of receipts and fees above those budgeted to the Enrollment Growth Reserve.
16 may allocate those receipts to the community colleges for operating costs according to a formula
17 adopted by the State Board. Funds in the Enrollment Growth Reserve allocated pursuant to this
18 subsection shall not revert to the General Fund and shall remain available to the State Board until
19 expended. The State Board may allocate funds in this reserve to colleges experiencing an
20 enrollment increase greater than five percent (5%) of budgeted enrollment levels."
21 SECTION 6.3.(f) G.S. 115D-31 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
