5 "§ 115D-21.10. Curriculum courses taught throughout year.
6 Community colleges may teach curriculum courses at any time during the year, including the
7 summer term. Student membership hours from these courses shall be counted when computing
8 full-time equivalent students (FTE) for use in budget funding formulas at the State level."
