29 school programs, as provided by Part 9 of Article 16 of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes.
30 "§ 115D-30.15. Noncredit courses.
31 Subject to rules adopted by the State Board of Community Colleges, local community
32 colleges may provide for the following:
33 (1) During the summer quarter, persons less than 16 years old may be permitted
34 to take noncredit courses on a self-supporting basis.
35 (2) High school students may be permitted to take noncredit courses in safe
36 driving on a self-supporting basis during the academic year or the summer.
