17 FISCAL RESPONSIBILITY AND COMMUNITY COLLEGE TECH PLANNING
18 SECTION 6.7. Chapter 115D of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
19 section to read:
20 "§ 115D-9.40. Evaluation of technology costs.
21 The State Board of Community Colleges shall adopt a policy that requires all community
22 colleges to evaluate the following when acquiring technology, computer hardware, and software:
23 (1) The long-term cost of ownership, including costs of repairing the technology,
24 computer hardware, or software.
25 (2) Any flexibility for innovation during the life of the technology, computer
26 hardware, or software.
27 (3) Any anticipated resale or salvage value at the end of the target life cycle for
28 the technology, computer hardware, or software based on the average resale
29 or salvage value of similar technology, computer hardware, or software as a
30 percentage of the initial cost of purchase."
31
32 EXPEDITED TEACHER PIPELINE PATHWAY STUDY
33 SECTION 6.8. No later than March 15, 2026, ApprenticeshipNC shall report to the
34 Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee on a plan to facilitate one or more expedited
35 pathways for apprenticeship candidates to enter the teaching profession. ApprenticeshipNC shall
36 develop the plan in collaboration with the Board of Governors of The University of North
37 Carolina, the State Board of Community Colleges, the Department of Public Instruction, and
38 Teach NC. In addition, ApprenticeshipNC may, in its discretion, collaborate with representatives
39 of approved educator preparation programs, local school administrative units, and existing
