49 SECTION 7.57. G.S. 115C-375.3 reads as rewritten:
50 "§ 115C-375.3. Guidelines to support and assist students with diabetes.
Page 158 Senate Bill 257-Fifth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (a) Local boards of education and boards of directors of charter schools Governing bodies
2 of public school units shall ensure that the guidelines adopted by the State Board of Education
3 under G.S. 115C-12(31) are implemented in schools in which students with diabetes are enrolled.
4 In particular, the boards shall require the implementation of the procedures set forth in those
5 guidelines for the development and implementation of individual diabetes care plans. The boards
6 also shall make available necessary information and staff development to teachers and school
7 personnel in order to appropriately support and assist students with diabetes in accordance with
8 their individual diabetes care plans.
9 (b) Governing bodies of public school units shall ensure that each school provides parents
10 and legal guardians with information about type 1 and type 2 diabetes at the beginning of every
11 school year. This information shall include all of the following:
12 (1) A description of type 1 and type 2 diabetes.
13 (2) A description of the risk factors and warning signs associated with type 1 and
14 type 2 diabetes.
15 (3) A recommendation that if a student is displaying warning signs associated
16 with diabetes, the parent or guardian of the student consult with the primary
17 care provider of the student to determine if immediate screening for diabetes
18 is appropriate.
19 (4) A description of the screening process for and stages of diabetes.
20 (5) A recommendation that if a student receives a diabetes diagnosis, the parent
21 or guardian of the student consult with the primary care provider of the student
22 to develop an appropriate treatment plan.
23 (6) Notification that the school is required to assist students with diabetes in
24 accordance with the rules adopted by the State Board of Education pursuant
25 to G.S. 115C-12(31)."
