27 MEDICAL CONDITION ACTION PLANS
28 SECTION 7.58.(a) G.S. 115C-12 is amended by adding the following new
29 subdivisions to read:
30 "(50) Medical Condition Action Plan. – The State Board of Education shall adopt a
31 rule establishing a medical condition action plan as provided in
32 G.S. 115C-375.1 to be implemented by each public school unit for each
33 student at risk for a medical emergency as diagnosed by a doctor.
34 (51) Medical Emergency Plan. – The State Board of Education, in consultation
35 with the Department of Public Instruction and the Department of Health and
36 Human Services, shall adopt a rule establishing the required response of
37 public school unit employees when a student has a medical emergency not
38 otherwise covered by a medical condition action plan implemented in
39 accordance with G.S. 115C-375.1. The Department of Public Instruction shall
40 provide each public school unit with a copy of the rule, and each public school
41 unit shall implement the rule."
