43 "§ 115C-375.1. To provide some medical care to students.students and implement medical
44 condition action plans.
45 (a) Notwithstanding G.S. 90-21.10B, it is within the scope of duty of teachers, including
46 substitute teachers, teacher assistants, student teachers, or any other public school employee
47 when authorized by the board of education governing body of a public school unit or its designee,
48 (i) to administer any drugs or medication prescribed by a doctor upon written request of the
49 parents, or as described in the medical condition action plan required by subsection (b) of this
50 section, (ii) to give emergency health care when reasonably apparent circumstances indicate that
51 any delay would seriously worsen the physical condition or endanger the life of the pupil, student,
