14 INSTITUTIONAL PERFORMANCE ACCOUNTABILITY AND FUNDING
15 SECTION 8.20. Part 2A of Article 1 of Chapter 116 of the General Statutes is
16 amended by adding the following new section to read:
17 "§ 116-30.10. Institutional performance accountability.
18 (a) Implementation of Accountability Measures and Performance Standards. – To the
19 extent funds are available to the Board of Governors pursuant to the provisions of this Chapter
20 or otherwise made available for this purpose, the Board of Governors may adopt and implement
21 a system of accountability measures and performance standards to be used to allocate those funds
22 to constituent institutions of The University of North Carolina.
23 (b) Recognition of Successful Institutional Performance. – The Board may allocate
24 available funds among constituent institutions based on an evaluation of the performance of each
25 institution conducted in accordance with the system of accountability measures and performance
26 standards adopted pursuant to subsection (a) of this section. The evaluation shall include at least
27 the following components:
28 (1) Performance change, based on the rate of student success at a constituent
29 institution as compared to the baseline or goal rate of student success for that
30 constituent institution.
31 (2) Institutional impact, based on the number of students at a constituent
32 institution who graduate with a degree.
33 (c) Institutional Support. – In addition to any funds allocated pursuant to subsection (b)
34 of this section, the Board of Governors may allocate available funds to specific constituent
35 institutions that require targeted support to increase performance or adapt to significant
36 enrollment changes. Funds allocated to an institution pursuant to this subsection may be used to
37 support strategies at the constituent institution to improve institutional performance."
