32 AUTHORIZE THE NORTH CAROLINA COLLABORATORY TO STUDY THE
33 INCLUSION OF THE CLASSIC LEARNING TEST AMONG STANDARDIZED
34 TESTS CONSIDERED FOR UNDERGRADUATE ADMISSION AND THE AWARD
35 OF SCHOLARSHIPS AT CONSTITUENT INSTITUTIONS OF THE UNIVERSITY
36 OF NORTH CAROLINA
37 SECTION 8.30.(a) The North Carolina Collaboratory shall study the viability of
38 including Classic Learning Test scores as a part of an application for admission or award of
39 scholarship to a constituent institution of The University of North Carolina. In conducting this
40 study, the Collaboratory shall seek input from The University of North Carolina and the James
41 G. Martin Center for Academic Renewal. As a part of the study, the Collaboratory shall
42 determine:
43 (1) Whether an applicant's score on the Classic Learning Test serves the purpose
44 of aiding constituent institutions in determining (i) an applicant's
45 qualifications for undergraduate admission and (ii) an applicant's
46 qualifications for award of scholarships funded in whole or in part with State
47 funds and administered by an entity of The University of North Carolina.
48 (2) Whether an applicant's performance on the Classic Learning Test is predictive
49 of college success.
50 (3) Whether a score on the Classic Learning Test can be deemed concordant with
51 a score on the SAT or ACT such that The University of North Carolina could
Senate Bill 257-Fifth Edition Page 197

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 use an applicant's score on the Classic Learning Test interchangeably with a
2 score on the SAT or ACT for the purposes of setting minimum requirements
3 for admission and awarding scholarships.
4 (4) The financial, operational, and administrative cost to The University of North
5 Carolina and constituent institutions associated with accepting an applicant's
6 score on the Classic Learning Test in addition to accepting an applicant's score
7 on the SAT or ACT.
8 (5) The financial, operational, and administrative cost to the State of adding the
9 CLT10 to the list of standardized tests offered one time and at no cost to the
10 student for every student in the eighth through tenth grades who has completed
11 Algebra I or who is in the last month of Algebra I pursuant to
12 G.S. 115C-174.18.
13 SECTION 8.30.(b) The Collaboratory shall make a final report on its study to the
14 Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee no later than December 15, 2025.
15 SECTION 8.30.(c) This section is effective when it becomes law.
