36 DEFINE SEPSIS/NORTH CAROLINA MEDICAID PROGRAM
37 SECTION 9E.21.(a) Except as provided in subsection (b) of this section, the
38 Department of Health and Human Services, Division of Health Benefits (DHB), shall ensure that
39 the Medicaid program (i) complies with the most recently published American College of Chest
40 Physicians/Society of Critical Care Medicine (ACCP/SCCM) sepsis guidelines, primarily known
41 as the Surviving Sepsis Campaign guidelines, and (ii) does not utilize any clinical criteria beyond
42 that described in the ACCP/SCCM sepsis guidelines when making any medical necessity or
43 utilization review determinations related to diagnosis, treatment, and management of sepsis.
44 DHB shall amend all relevant clinical coverage policies and rules, or adopt rules, policies, or
45 guidelines, necessary to implement this section.
46 SECTION 9E.21.(b) The Department of Health and Human Services, Division of
47 Health Benefits, shall not make any changes to the Medicaid program described in this section if
48 those changes exceed the authority of the Division of Health Benefits under G.S. 108A-54(e)(1)
49 or creates a recurring cost to the State that would reasonably be anticipated to exceed a future
50 authorized budget for the Medicaid program.
51 SECTION 9E.21.(c) This section is effective when it becomes law.
