20 PART IX-H. PUBLIC HEALTH
21
22 LOCAL HEALTH DEPARTMENTS/COMPETITIVE GRANT PROCESS TO
23 IMPROVE MATERNAL AND CHILD HEALTH
24 SECTION 9H.1.(a) Funds appropriated in this act to the Department of Health and
25 Human Services, Division of Public Health, for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium to
26 award competitive grants to local health departments for the improvement of maternal and child
27 health shall be used to continue administering a competitive grant process for local health
28 departments based on maternal and infant health indicators and the county's detailed proposal to
29 invest in evidence-based programs to achieve the following goals:
30 (1) Improve North Carolina's birth outcomes.
31 (2) Improve the overall health status of children in this State from birth to age 5.
32 (3) Lower the State's infant mortality rate.
33 SECTION 9H.1.(b) The plan for administering the competitive grant process shall
34 include at least all of the following components:
35 (1) A request for application (RFA) process to allow local health departments to
36 apply for and receive State funds on a competitive basis. The Department shall
37 require local health departments to include in the application a plan to evaluate
38 the effectiveness, including measurable impact or outcomes, of the activities,
39 services, and programs for which the funds are being requested.
40 (2) A requirement that the Secretary prioritize grant awards to those local health
41 departments that are able to leverage non-State funds in addition to the grant
42 award.
43 (3) Ensures that funds received by the Department to implement the plan
44 supplement and do not supplant existing funds for maternal and child health
45 initiatives.
46 (4) Allows grants to be awarded to local health departments for up to three years.
47 SECTION 9H.1.(c) No later than July 1 of each year, as applicable, the Secretary
48 shall announce the recipients of the competitive grant awards and allocate funds to the grant
49 recipients for the respective grant period. After awards have been granted, the Secretary shall
50 submit a report to the Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on Health and Human Services on
51 the grant awards that includes at least all of the following:
