30 SECTION 17.10.(a) Section 19C.10 of S.L. 2021-180, as amended by Section 5.3
31 of S.L. 2025-2, reads as rewritten:
32 "SECTION 19C.10.(a) Notwithstanding G.S. 162-58, and consistent with the provisions of
33 Article 3 of Chapter 148 of the General Statutes, sheriffs having custody of inmates under the
34 Statewide Misdemeanant Confinement Program may utilize those inmates to maintain the
35 cleanliness of areas along local and State roadways, which may include the removal of debris
36 resulting from a major disaster declaration by the President of the United States under the
37 Stafford Act (P.L. 93-288) or a disaster declared by the Governor under G.S. 166A-19.21.
38 "SECTION 19C.10.(b) For purposes of this section, the following definitions shall apply:
39 (1) Housing night. – A night spent by an individual inmate in the custody of the
40 sheriff pursuant to the Statewide Misdemeanant Confinement Program.
41 (1)(1a) Road mile. – A section of roadside equaling 1 mile in length, not including
42 any roadsides that are parallel to that section.
43 (2) Work hour. – An hour worked by an individual inmate, including time spent
44 traveling to and from work sites and break time taken during work efforts.
45 "SECTION 19C.10.(c) A sheriff that utilizes inmates pursuant to subsection (a) of this
46 section shall coordinate with the Department of Transportation before and after a cleanup project
47 to ensure that cleanup efforts are not unnecessarily duplicated by either the sheriff's office or the
48 Department of Transportation. The sheriff shall also ensure that all inmates utilized pursuant to
49 this subsection are appropriately guarded while working and that food, water, and bathroom
50 facilities are accessible in reasonable amounts and times.
