13 STUDY NONPUBLIC EDUCATION
14 SECTION 22.5.(a) The Joint Legislative Oversight Committee on General
15 Government shall study the duties and responsibilities of the Department of Administration,
16 Division of Nonpublic Education, including the following:
17 (1) Whether all of the Division's statutory duties are currently being performed.
18 (2) The manner in which the statutory duties are being performed, such as online
19 posting of information or in-person interaction, and the overall effectiveness
20 of the different approaches used to provide information and other assistance
21 to nonpublic students and their families.
22 (3) If the statutory duties should be amended in any way to better serve nonpublic
23 school students and their families.
24 (4) Whether other State or local government agencies are able to assume some or
25 all of the statutory duties in a way that does not unnecessarily disrupt the
26 provision of services to nonpublic school students and their families.
27 (5) Any other matters deemed relevant to the purpose of the study.
28 SECTION 22.5.(b) The Division of Nonpublic Education shall provide any
29 information requested by the Committee to conduct the study. By May 15, 2026, the Committee
30 shall make recommendations on its findings and conclusions, including proposed legislation, to
31 the Senate Appropriations Committee on General Government and Information Technology, the
32 House of Representatives Appropriations Committee on General Government, and the Fiscal
33 Research Division.
