29 GRANT EMPLOYING AGENCY FLEXIBILITY/HIRING/PAY/CLASSIFICATION
30 SECTION 41.21E.(a) Article 1 of Chapter 126 of the General Statutes is amended
31 by adding a new section to read:
32 "§ 126-3.1. Employing agency flexibility.
33 (a) For the purposes of this section, an "employing agency" means the Council of State,
34 State agencies in the executive branch of government, the Community College System Office,
35 and The University of North Carolina.
36 (b) An employing agency is granted flexibility, notwithstanding other provisions of this
37 Chapter to the contrary, to do all of the following:
38 (1) Offer qualified applicants for employment the option to have their
39 applications considered for future positions at the same agency and at other
40 agencies within the same or comparable classification.
41 (2) Permit agencies to recruit and hire applicants from job postings that apply to
42 all vacancies in a particular classification across all State agencies.
43 (3) Classify or reclassify positions according to the State Human Resources
44 Commission (SHRC) classification system, provided employees meet the
45 minimum requirements for the classification.
46 (4) Establish employee salaries within SHRC-determined salary ranges for
47 respective position classifications.
48 (c) Nothing in this section diminishes the powers of the State Human Resources
49 Commission or the Director of the Office of State Human Resources under any other provision
50 of this Chapter or relating to corrective actions taken when an employing agency fails to comply
51 with this section."
