45 (a) Appropriations made by an act of the General Assembly for capital improvements are
46 for constructing, repairing, or renovating State buildings, utilities, and other capital facilities; for
47 acquiring sites for them where necessary; for acquiring buildings and land for State government
48 purposes and other purposes as set forth in G.S. 143C-4-3.1; and shall be disbursed for the
49 purposes provided by that act. Expenditure of funds shall not be made by any State department,
50 institution, or agency until an allotment has been issued by the Governor as Director of the
51 Budget, which shall not be unreasonably withheld. The allotment shall be issued upon
