14 MODIFY SPORTS WAGERING REVENUE DISTRIBUTION
15 SECTION 44.5.(a) G.S. 105-113.128 reads as rewritten:
16 "§ 105-113.128. Use of tax proceeds.
17 The Secretary shall distribute the taxes collected under this Article, less the allowance to the
18 Department of Revenue and reimbursement to the Lottery Commission for administrative
19 expenses, in accordance with this section. The Secretary may retain the cost of administering this
20 Article, not to exceed five hundred thousand dollars ($500,000) a year, as reimbursement to the
21 Department. The Lottery Commission shall, no later than 20 days after the end of the month,
22 notify the Department of its unreimbursed expenses from administering the provisions of Article
23 9 of Chapter 18C of the General Statutes from the previous month. The Department shall
24 reimburse the Lottery Commission from the tax revenues collected under this Article no later
25 than the end of the month in which the Department was notified. The Secretary shall credit the
26 remainder of the net proceeds of the tax collected under this Article are to be credited in the
27 following priority:
28 (1) Two million dollars ($2,000,000) annually to the Department of Health and
29 Human Services for gambling addiction education and treatment programs.
30 (2) One million dollars ($1,000,000) annually to North Carolina Amateur Sports
31 to expand opportunities for persons up to age 18 to engage in youth sports,
32 which shall be distributed through a grant program. In making individual
33 grants, North Carolina Amateur Sports shall comply with the following:
34 a. Awards shall be used to provide for the purchase of youth sports
35 equipment, or to provide for public facility upgrades or improvements
36 which would benefit youth sports.
37 b. Awards may be given only to applicants who are either local
38 governments, including local school administrative units, or nonprofit
39 organizations exempt from taxation under section 501(c)(3) of the
40 Internal Revenue Code.
41 c. Awards may be given only to applicants who demonstrate that a
42 primary purpose for the funding is to facilitate opportunities for
43 persons up to age 18 to engage in youth sports.
44 d. The total dollar amount awarded each year to all applicants in any one
45 county may not exceed one percent (1%) of the total funding available
46 on July 1 of that year.
47 (3) Three hundred thousand dollars ($300,000) The following amounts annually
48 shall be appropriated to each of the institutions listed public universities as
49 provided and that meet the criteria in this subdivision to support collegiate
50 athletic departments. If there are not sufficient funds for each of these
51 institutions the public universities to receive an appropriation of three hundred
